{}','{}'),(1016,268284,'Libra','{}','{}'),(1017,282647,'Luna','{}','{}'),(1018,279182,'Mars','{}','{}'),(1019,274633,'Megrez','{}','{}'),(1020,274634,'Merak','{}','{}'),(1021,282645,'Mercurius','{}','{}'),(1022,279184,'Minamijuuji, Sei','{}','{}'),(1023,281732,'Nick','{}','{}'),(1024,268286,'Parthenos','{}','{}'),(1025,281733,'Richard','{}','{}'),(1026,282644,'Saturnus','{}','{}'),(1027,281731,'Shuu','{}','{}'),(1028,282646,'Sol','{}','{}'),(1029,268287,'Virgo','{}','{}'),(1030,269906,'Light','{\"Description\":\"A human boy. Possessing the rare gift \\u0022Unlimited Gacha,\\u0022 he joins the adventurer party \\u0022the Concord of the Tribes,\\u0022 but is betrayed by the comrades he trusted, and swears revenge.\",\"(Source\":\"Official site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"A human boy. Possessing the rare gift \\\"Unlimited Gacha,\\\" he joins the adventurer party \\\"the Concord of the Tribes,\\\" but is betrayed by the comrades he trusted, and swears revenge.\"}'),(1031,269907,'Mei','{\"Description\":\"Level 9999 Ever-Seeking Maid. The first SUR (Super Ultra Rare) card Light drew in \\u0022the Abyss.\\u0022 She swears absolute loyalty to Light, supporting his revenge with combat and espionage abilities.\",\"(Source\":\"Official site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 9999 Ever-Seeking Maid. The first SUR (Super Ultra Rare) card Light drew in \\\"the Abyss.\\\" She swears absolute loyalty to Light, supporting his revenge with combat and espionage abilities.\"}'),(1032,275768,'Aoyuki','{\"Description\":\"Level 9999 Genius Monster Tamer. Commands all manner of magical beasts and divine creatures, using them for combat and intelligence gathering. Wears a hood with cat ears and usually only says \\u0022nya.\\u0022\",\"(Source\":\"Official Site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official Site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 9999 Genius Monster Tamer. Commands all manner of magical beasts and divine creatures, using them for combat and intelligence gathering. Wears a hood with cat ears and usually only says \\\"nya.\\\"\"}'),(1033,283431,'Chancellor','{}','{}'),(1034,280146,'Diablo','{\"Description\":\"A fighter from the demon race who is at level 403.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A fighter from the demon race who is at level 403.\"}'),(1035,280143,'Drago','{\"Description\":\"A warrior from the race of dragonutes. His level is 512. Drago is the leader of the adventurer group Concord of the Tribes which Light was part of. Even when he looks like a prudent and friendly person, Drago was the one who ordered the others to kill Light and disguise the murder as a monster attack.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A warrior from the race of dragonutes. His level is 512. Drago is the leader of the adventurer group Concord of the Tribes which Light was part of. Even when he looks like a prudent and friendly person, Drago was the one who ordered the others to kill Light and disguise the murder as a monster attack.\"}'),(1036,280671,'Due','{}','{}'),(1037,281669,'Elio','{}','{}'),(1038,275769,'Ellie','{\"Description\":\"Level 9999 Forbidden Witch. Master of all magic and sorcery, responsible for analyzing and controlling the dungeon core of \\u0022Abyss.\\u0022 Worships Light as \\u0022Lord Light\\u0022 and shows no mercy to enemies.\",\"(Source\":\"Official Site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official Site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 9999 Forbidden Witch. Master of all magic and sorcery, responsible for analyzing and controlling the dungeon core of \\\"Abyss.\\\" Worships Light as \\\"Lord Light\\\" and shows no mercy to enemies.\"}'),(1039,280150,'Garou','{\"Description\":\"A warrior from the beast men tribe, Garou is a wolf man who fights his opponents with his claws. His level is at 151. Garou was ordered by Drago to deal the final blow on Light. Before Garou was able to kill the young boy, Light escaped activating a teleportation trap by accident.\",\"Description_2\":\"After Light was declared dead, Garou became popular among the beast man tribe. In reality, Garou is a coward and would betray his own friends in order to survive. As his tribe is one of the weakest (second only to humans), he has no information regarding the mission of the Concord of the Tribes or about the master.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A warrior from the beast men tribe, Garou is a wolf man who fights his opponents with his claws. His level is at 151. Garou was ordered by Drago to deal the final blow on Light. Before Garou was able to kill the young boy, Light escaped activating a teleportation trap by accident.\", \"Description_2\": \"After Light was declared dead, Garou became popular among the beast man tribe. In reality, Garou is a coward and would betray his own friends in order to survive. As his tribe is one of the weakest (second only to humans), he has no information regarding the mission of the Concord of the Tribes or about the master.\"}'),(1040,282098,'Gilbert','{}','{}'),(1041,281672,'Gimra','{}','{}'),(1042,275771,'Gold','{\"Description\":\"Level 5000 Auric Knight. He refers to himself with \\u0022Wagahai\\u0022 (a Japanese pronoun meaning \\u0022I\\u0022 or \\u0022myself,\\u0022 often implying grandeur). He is clad in a very conspicuous golden armor and boasts of his iron-clad defenses. Acts as the tank alongside Light and others in the adventurer party \\u0022Black Fools.\\u0022\",\"(Source\":\"Official site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 5000 Auric Knight. He refers to himself with \\\"Wagahai\\\" (a Japanese pronoun meaning \\\"I\\\" or \\\"myself,\\\" often implying grandeur). He is clad in a very conspicuous golden armor and boasts of his iron-clad defenses. Acts as the tank alongside Light and others in the adventurer party \\\"Black Fools.\\\"\"}'),(1043,283094,'Hardy','{}','{}'),(1044,280670,'Hifumi','{}','{}'),(1045,280355,'Iceheat','{\"Description\":\"A Level 7777 grappler maid who is a strict disciplinarian. Wields powerful fire and ice magic.\",\"(Source\":\"Light Novel)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Light Novel)\", \"Description\": \"A Level 7777 grappler maid who is a strict disciplinarian. Wields powerful fire and ice magic.\"}'),(1046,280667,'Jack','{\"Description\":\"A Level 7777 fighter with top-level defensive abilities. Considers himself Light\\u0027s \\u0022bro,\\u0022 even though Light is his boss.\",\"(Source\":\"Light Novel)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Light Novel)\", \"Description\": \"A Level 7777 fighter with top-level defensive abilities. Considers himself Light\'s \\\"bro,\\\" even though Light is his boss.\"}'),(1047,283091,'Khia','{}','{}'),(1048,281670,'Kyto','{}','{}'),(1049,283375,'Lif','{}','{}'),(1050,283092,'Lock','{}','{}'),(1051,280669,'Mea','{}','{}'),(1052,281286,'Mera','{\"Description\":\"A Level 7777 chimera capable of shapeshifting, anatomical separation, and predation. One of the most frightening warriors at Light\\u0027s command, who swears absolute fealty to her master.\",\"(Source\":\"Light Novel)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Light Novel)\", \"Description\": \"A Level 7777 chimera capable of shapeshifting, anatomical separation, and predation. One of the most frightening warriors at Light\'s command, who swears absolute fealty to her master.\"}'),(1053,283054,'Mikhael','{}','{}'),(1054,281668,'Miya','{}','{}'),(1055,283433,'Mohawk Leader','{}','{}'),(1056,283095,'Muste','{}','{}'),(1057,280147,'Naano','{\"Description\":\"A smith from the dwarven tribe whose goal is to create a godlike weapon. His level is 301. Due to his fame he was chosen by the dwarven king to join the Concord of the Tribes to observe Light and his gift.\",\"Description_2\":\"After the mission was accomplished, Naano became addicted to alcohol because he failed to reach his own goal and was denied a second chance to look for the \\u0022master\\u0022 which he blamed Light for.\",\"Description_3\":\"Naano tests his forged weapons on humans. One day he received an instruction Manual for smithing a holy weapon by a mysterious merchant.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A smith from the dwarven tribe whose goal is to create a godlike weapon. His level is 301. Due to his fame he was chosen by the dwarven king to join the Concord of the Tribes to observe Light and his gift.\", \"Description_2\": \"After the mission was accomplished, Naano became addicted to alcohol because he failed to reach his own goal and was denied a second chance to look for the \\\"master\\\" which he blamed Light for.\", \"Description_3\": \"Naano tests his forged weapons on humans. One day he received an instruction Manual for smithing a holy weapon by a mysterious merchant.\"}'),(1058,283432,'Nanny','{}','{}'),(1059,275766,'Nazuna','{\"Description\":\"Level 9999 Ancestral Vampire Knight. The strongest member of the \\u0022Abyss\\u0022 group, wielding a massive greatsword with ease. Not great at thinking, but a lively mood-maker full of energy.\",\"(Source\":\"Official Site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official Site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 9999 Ancestral Vampire Knight. The strongest member of the \\\"Abyss\\\" group, wielding a massive greatsword with ease. Not great at thinking, but a lively mood-maker full of energy.\"}'),(1060,275770,'Nemumu','{\"Description\":\"Level 5000 Assassin\\u0027s Blade. A dual-wielding dagger assassin. Excels in stealth operations, eliminating targets without being noticed. Acts alongside Light and others as a member of the adventurer party \\u0022Black Fools.\\u0022\",\"(Source\":\"Official site, translated)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Official site, translated)\", \"Description\": \"Level 5000 Assassin\'s Blade. A dual-wielding dagger assassin. Excels in stealth operations, eliminating targets without being noticed. Acts alongside Light and others as a member of the adventurer party \\\"Black Fools.\\\"\"}'),(1061,283090,'Nhia','{}','{}'),(1062,280145,'Oboro','{\"Description\":\"A ghoul warrior at level 419. He is the second strongest member of the Concord of the Tribes right after Drago.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A ghoul warrior at level 419. He is the second strongest member of the Concord of the Tribes right after Drago.\"}'),(1063,280668,'Prime','{}','{}'),(1064,280149,'Santor','{\"Description\":\"A warrior from the centaur tribe whose level is at 152.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A warrior from the centaur tribe whose level is at 152.\"}'),(1065,280144,'Sasha','{\"Description\":\"An archer from the elven tribe. Her level is 308. She was born as a result of an affair between a nobleman and a commoner, which is why she was disowned by her family.\",\"Description_2\":\"She seemingly had feelings for Light which turned out to be a lie, which is why the other members of the Concord of the Tribes mocked her.\",\"Description_3\":\"After seemingly killing Light and her engagement with a high-ranked elf, her reputation within her race and family increased. When she learned that Light was still alive she tried to kill him in order to keep her reputation. Instead she was captured by Light, after she failed to kill him.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"An archer from the elven tribe. Her level is 308. She was born as a result of an affair between a nobleman and a commoner, which is why she was disowned by her family.\", \"Description_2\": \"She seemingly had feelings for Light which turned out to be a lie, which is why the other members of the Concord of the Tribes mocked her.\", \"Description_3\": \"After seemingly killing Light and her engagement with a high-ranked elf, her reputation within her race and family increased. When she learned that Light was still alive she tried to kill him in order to keep her reputation. Instead she was captured by Light, after she failed to kill him.\"}'),(1066,283093,'Sharphat','{}','{}'),(1067,280148,'Sionne','{\"Description\":\"A young woman and researcher from the dark elf tribe at level 304. Sionne is considered a prodigy and was able to graduate at a renowned university where people from all races can study without facing discrimination.\",\"Description_2\":\"She became a professor at the university and was fired after it was discovered that she used humans for her research about the \\u0022gift\\u0022. Due to the loss of her professorship and her source of income, she decided to work as an adventurer and was soon scouted to become a member of the Concord of the Tribes.\",\"Description_3\":\"To her, her research has the highest priority which is why she shows no emotions, neither towards humans nor to her own tribe. She is willing to sacrifice each and everyone as long as she can accomplish her goals in her research. Sionne made a pact with a soul dragon, a monster from another world in hopes to reach her goal.\",\"(Source\":\"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Mugen Gacha Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"A young woman and researcher from the dark elf tribe at level 304. Sionne is considered a prodigy and was able to graduate at a renowned university where people from all races can study without facing discrimination.\", \"Description_2\": \"She became a professor at the university and was fired after it was discovered that she used humans for her research about the \\\"gift\\\". Due to the loss of her professorship and her source of income, she decided to work as an adventurer and was soon scouted to become a member of the Concord of the Tribes.\", \"Description_3\": \"To her, her research has the highest priority which is why she shows no emotions, neither towards humans nor to her own tribe. She is willing to sacrifice each and everyone as long as she can accomplish her goals in her research. Sionne made a pact with a soul dragon, a monster from another world in hopes to reach her goal.\"}'),(1068,283430,'Soscha','{}','{}'),(1069,282097,'Suvellan','{}','{}'),(1070,275162,'Suzu','{\"Description\":\"A superior Level 7777 musketeer who is also incredibly shy. Wields Lock the magical talking musket as her trusty weapon.\",\"(Source\":\"Light Novel)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Light Novel)\", \"Description\": \"A superior Level 7777 musketeer who is also incredibly shy. Wields Lock the magical talking musket as her trusty weapon.\"}'),(1071,281673,'Wordy','{}','{}'),(1072,281671,'Yanaaq','{}','{}'),(1073,277769,'Amoru','{}','{}'),(1074,274118,'Himegami, Akira','{}','{}'),(1075,274119,'Yuugure','{}','{}'),(1076,279512,'Ajisai','{}','{}'),(1077,283342,'Caelo','{}','{}'),(1078,279962,'Caniss','{}','{}'),(1079,279510,'Casuta','{}','{}'),(1080,278341,'Hakubo','{}','{}'),(1081,279513,'Haniyama','{}','{}'),(1082,279516,'Idhi','{}','{}'),(1083,280945,'Lieutenant Colonel Yamabuki','{}','{}'),(1084,279514,'Lontano, Kalcrom','{}','{}'),(1085,279515,'Lontano, Fides','{}','{}'),(1086,283343,'Luv','{}','{}'),(1087,279963,'Marlum','{}','{}'),(1088,278342,'Oboro','{}','{}'),(1089,274120,'Oumagi, Towasa','{}','{}'),(1090,279965,'Seshat','{}','{}'),(1091,280330,'Taverina','{}','{}'),(1092,279964,'Urus','{}','{}'),(1093,279511,'Vare','{}','{}'),(1094,280331,'Vogt','{}','{}'),(1095,280329,'Weir','{}','{}'),(1096,278339,'Yoiyami','{}','{}'),(1097,278343,'Yokurata','{}','{}'),(1098,668,'Saotome, Ranma','{\"Description\":\"Training with Genma at Jusenkyo in China, Ranma was thrown into a spring called Nyanniichuan. He emerged as a young girl, according with the spring\\u0027s curse. When splashed with hot water, he changes back to a boy, but when splashed with cold to room temperature water, he turns into a girl again. As for our well-built 16-year-old hero/heroine, the martial arts is his life. He also possesses a rather large and easily wounded ego, believing his physical strength to be his only virtue. Whenever his pride is damaged, Ranma feels the need to rectify the situation, even when it\\u0027s not necessarily in his best interest to do so.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Training with Genma at Jusenkyo in China, Ranma was thrown into a spring called Nyanniichuan. He emerged as a young girl, according with the spring\'s curse. When splashed with hot water, he changes back to a boy, but when splashed with cold to room temperature water, he turns into a girl again. As for our well-built 16-year-old hero/heroine, the martial arts is his life. He also possesses a rather large and easily wounded ego, believing his physical strength to be his only virtue. Whenever his pride is damaged, Ranma feels the need to rectify the situation, even when it\'s not necessarily in his best interest to do so.\"}'),(1099,669,'Tendou, Akane','{\"Height\":\"1.57 m\",\"Hobbies\":\"Martial arts (especially for anger-management), sports\",\"Description\":\"Akane is far from being delicate and her exuberant, life-loving demeanor is apparent in everything she does. Although she appears to be non-klutzy on the movement scale, she\\u0027s a lead weight in the water.\",\"Description_2\":\"Her eyes are a dark blue (brown in the anime), almost black. She has an unextraordinary nose, and a cute smile. Akane\\u0027s navy blue hair is cut short and sort of boyishly (initially the cutting of her hair was accidental, but she grew to love it after accepting her long hair did not reflect her as well as it did on her sister Kasumi).\",\"Description_3\":\"She doesn\\u0027t like being called a \\u0022tomboy,\\u0022 \\u0022ugly,\\u0022 or \\u0022uncute.\\u0022 It is quite possibly the fastest way to get malleted by Akane. The second fastest way to get malleted by Akane is to grope her. She very much dislikes perverts, nor does she like being groped. However, the usual perverts of Nerima seem to slip by much easier than Ranma does who apparently is a subconscious pervert and is always getting malleted by Akane for being in the wrong place at the wrong time.\",\"Description_4\":\"Akane is a fiery young beauty. She doesn\\u0027t like to be dominated or told how she should act or be. Most importantly, she is herself.\",\"Description_5\":\"Despite what some people would tell, Akane is a very complex person. She had different attitudes toward different people\\u2014to most, she would be a sweet, good-natured person with just a hint of a quick temper. To Ranma, though, she comes off as a man-hating, violent tomboy. First impressions are a big deal with her.\",\"Akane has a problem with acting feminine. This is because she\\u0027s had very few female role models in her life, besides Kasumi, whom for a great many years Akane modeled herself after. Almost anything that the Japanese attribute to females\":\"tea ceremony, gymnastics, etc., Akane struggles with. Even society\\u0027s rules on how a girl should act in a relationship, she defies.\",\"Description_6\":\"Akane has lived in the Tendou Dojo with her two sisters and father all of her life. Her mother died when she was young, and therefore for most her childhood Akane was raised by her eldest sister, Kasumi, and her father, Soun.\"}','{\"Height\": \"1.57 m\", \"Hobbies\": \"Martial arts (especially for anger-management), sports\", \"Description\": \"Akane is far from being delicate and her exuberant, life-loving demeanor is apparent in everything she does. Although she appears to be non-klutzy on the movement scale, she\'s a lead weight in the water.\", \"Description_2\": \"Her eyes are a dark blue (brown in the anime), almost black. She has an unextraordinary nose, and a cute smile. Akane\'s navy blue hair is cut short and sort of boyishly (initially the cutting of her hair was accidental, but she grew to love it after accepting her long hair did not reflect her as well as it did on her sister Kasumi).\", \"Description_3\": \"She doesn\'t like being called a \\\"tomboy,\\\" \\\"ugly,\\\" or \\\"uncute.\\\" It is quite possibly the fastest way to get malleted by Akane. The second fastest way to get malleted by Akane is to grope her. She very much dislikes perverts, nor does she like being groped. However, the usual perverts of Nerima seem to slip by much easier than Ranma does who apparently is a subconscious pervert and is always getting malleted by Akane for being in the wrong place at the wrong time.\", \"Description_4\": \"Akane is a fiery young beauty. She doesn\'t like to be dominated or told how she should act or be. Most importantly, she is herself.\", \"Description_5\": \"Despite what some people would tell, Akane is a very complex person. She had different attitudes toward different people—to most, she would be a sweet, good-natured person with just a hint of a quick temper. To Ranma, though, she comes off as a man-hating, violent tomboy. First impressions are a big deal with her.\", \"Description_6\": \"Akane has lived in the Tendou Dojo with her two sisters and father all of her life. Her mother died when she was young, and therefore for most her childhood Akane was raised by her eldest sister, Kasumi, and her father, Soun.\", \"Akane has a problem with acting feminine. This is because she\'s had very few female role models in her life, besides Kasumi, whom for a great many years Akane modeled herself after. Almost anything that the Japanese attribute to females\": \"tea ceremony, gymnastics, etc., Akane struggles with. Even society\'s rules on how a girl should act in a relationship, she defies.\"}');
INSERT INTO `Characters` VALUES (1100,24764,'Cologne','{\"Description\":\"Cologne is the great-grandmother of Shampoo. She accompanies Shampoo on her return to Japan, and opens the Cat Caf\\u00E9 in Furinkan. She is a contemporary of Happosai, and well over one hundred years old. She calls Ranma \\u0022bride-groom\\u0022 and \\u0022son-in-law\\u0022 due to her attempts to have him marry Shampoo, and just to watch him become enraged. She is a grand master of martial arts, and occasionally teaches Ranma and his rivals new techniques. She gets around by pogoing on a gnarled wooden staff that she sometimes uses as a weapon.\",\"Description_2\":\"She is the grand master of the Chinese Amazon martial arts, allowing her to manipulate water and ice, create whirlwinds using an opponent\\u0027s aura against them, shatter inanimate objects with a simple touch, and touch pressure points to make a person feel like they are burning with even the slightest amount of heat. Cologne is knowledgeable in several other disciplines such as arcane lore, cooking, Chinese mythology, and magic artifacts.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Cologne is the great-grandmother of Shampoo. She accompanies Shampoo on her return to Japan, and opens the Cat Café in Furinkan. She is a contemporary of Happosai, and well over one hundred years old. She calls Ranma \\\"bride-groom\\\" and \\\"son-in-law\\\" due to her attempts to have him marry Shampoo, and just to watch him become enraged. She is a grand master of martial arts, and occasionally teaches Ranma and his rivals new techniques. She gets around by pogoing on a gnarled wooden staff that she sometimes uses as a weapon.\", \"Description_2\": \"She is the grand master of the Chinese Amazon martial arts, allowing her to manipulate water and ice, create whirlwinds using an opponent\'s aura against them, shatter inanimate objects with a simple touch, and touch pressure points to make a person feel like they are burning with even the slightest amount of heat. Cologne is knowledgeable in several other disciplines such as arcane lore, cooking, Chinese mythology, and magic artifacts.\"}'),(1101,244445,'Dojo Destroyer','{}','{}'),(1102,10813,'Gosunkugi, Hikaru','{}','{}'),(1103,17171,'Happosai','{\"Description\":\"Soun and Genma trained during their youths with the evil and perverted Happosai. The little man is THE master of Anything Goes Martial arts (Musabetsu Kakut\\u014D Ry\\u016B). He is also a panty thief and lecher beyond belief. In return for training, he berated and cajoled his two unwilling students into helping him with his panty raids and peeping expeditions. More often than not, they would end up humiliated or injured in the process. Once they had finally finished their training (i.e., escaped), they were able to get on with their lives. That is, until Happosai returned to select the next Anything Goes master.\",\"Description_2\":\"What he found when he reached the Tendou Dojo was Ranma. Disgustingly enough, Happosai leched onto girl-type Ranma, even though he knows Ranma is a boy.\",\"Description_3\":\"Taking up residence at the Tendou Dojo, he began extending Ranma\\u0027s training. He also began to expand his panty raids into the surrounding neighborhood, as well as the Tendou girls\\u0027 bedrooms.\",\"Description_4\":\"Happosai is a tiny, yet immensely powerful martial artist. He usually wears a purple coverall, or occasionally a green bathing suit. When on his panty raids, he often wears a scarf as a mask. He is bald, with white fringes and a white moustache.\",\"Description_5\":\"Happosai is a master martial artist and deceptively strong for his size. His only real weakness is his perverted nature. Happosai would leap in front of a speeding train for a pair of girl\\u0027s panties. Often times he is foiled by a well placed bra, and if he cannot lech onto some poor, unsuspecting girl, or Ranma, he goes into an addict\\u0027s withdrawal syndrome. His power comes entirely from his lust, and he can be easily defeated by denying it.\",\"Description_6\":\"Happosai is master of many magical martial arts attacks, although many are really just special effects. For example, his world feared \\u0022Happo-dai-karin\\u0022 (Happo Fire Blast) Technique is really just a firework and a match. He does however, possess several powerful special energy techniques, as well.\",\"(Source\":\"GeoCities, edited)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"GeoCities, edited)\", \"Description\": \"Soun and Genma trained during their youths with the evil and perverted Happosai. The little man is THE master of Anything Goes Martial arts (Musabetsu Kakutō Ryū). He is also a panty thief and lecher beyond belief. In return for training, he berated and cajoled his two unwilling students into helping him with his panty raids and peeping expeditions. More often than not, they would end up humiliated or injured in the process. Once they had finally finished their training (i.e., escaped), they were able to get on with their lives. That is, until Happosai returned to select the next Anything Goes master.\", \"Description_2\": \"What he found when he reached the Tendou Dojo was Ranma. Disgustingly enough, Happosai leched onto girl-type Ranma, even though he knows Ranma is a boy.\", \"Description_3\": \"Taking up residence at the Tendou Dojo, he began extending Ranma\'s training. He also began to expand his panty raids into the surrounding neighborhood, as well as the Tendou girls\' bedrooms.\", \"Description_4\": \"Happosai is a tiny, yet immensely powerful martial artist. He usually wears a purple coverall, or occasionally a green bathing suit. When on his panty raids, he often wears a scarf as a mask. He is bald, with white fringes and a white moustache.\", \"Description_5\": \"Happosai is a master martial artist and deceptively strong for his size. His only real weakness is his perverted nature. Happosai would leap in front of a speeding train for a pair of girl\'s panties. Often times he is foiled by a well placed bra, and if he cannot lech onto some poor, unsuspecting girl, or Ranma, he goes into an addict\'s withdrawal syndrome. His power comes entirely from his lust, and he can be easily defeated by denying it.\", \"Description_6\": \"Happosai is master of many magical martial arts attacks, although many are really just special effects. For example, his world feared \\\"Happo-dai-karin\\\" (Happo Fire Blast) Technique is really just a firework and a match. He does however, possess several powerful special energy techniques, as well.\"}'),(1104,2369,'Hibiki, Ryouga','{\"Description\":\"Ryouga stands out in the crowd due to his regularly rough appearance. He spends much of his time wandering, often depressed over having to spend so much of his time alone in the wilderness, with the slightest rain turning him into a defenceless pig at the mercy of hungry humans or animals. His most notable characteristic is that, like his parents, and even his entire family, he has no sense of direction whatsoever. He is unable to go the right way, often sticking to the letter of any directions given to him, regardless of whether the path eventually turns. He has an inability to understand even the simplest of directions or draw any legible maps, once running the wrong way at the start of a three-legged race.\",\"Description_2\":\"This is not due to lack of motivation, however. For instance, on the way to a date, he was supposed to follow the edge of a lake, to reach a statue in plain sight directly in front of him. Instead, Ryouga follows a brook and gets lost again. In the anime, Maomolin the bakeneko possesses Ryouga and tries to lead him towards the girl he loves. However, Maomolin had as much trouble navigating as Ryouga himself even though the former was doing the thinking. In real world terms, he would be classified as suffering from autistic limitation or brain damage in this area. It is also possible that his lack of direction might be some form of family curse.\",\"Description_3\":\"In the anime this condition is worsened by Ryouga\\u0027s ability to traverse obscene distances in surprisingly little time on foot, although how he does this is unknown. When the two problems are combined, it results in Ryouga having essentially no idea where he is at any given time, which allows him to miss his destinations by insane margins. In one case, he attempted to reach Hokkaido and instead ended up in Hong Kong. Luckily, he carries a backpack, which evidently contains essentials for survival in the wild.\",\"Description_4\":\"In the manga this is not as heavily implied to be a supernatural talent, at least not beyond his comical tendency to pop up at odd moments. He seems to need much longer travel times, and has not explicitly been seen to swiftly and randomly traverse continents under his own power. However, in his first appearance he quickly overshot Tokyo by 500 miles twice in a row, apparently within the span of one or two days, though no explicit reference was given. Through the aid of the Kinjakan, he also quickly made it all the way from Jusenkyo to Moscow and back while out to get some dumplings in Peking. His map was also once shown to contain a forest, a caf\\u00E9, a road with a red car, the Tendo dojo, some African tribesmen, China, and France.\",\"Description_5\":\"Ryouga\\u0027s family house is within sight of Mount Fuji, where his dog Shirokuro (Checkers in the English translation) and her puppies live. However, given the Hibiki family\\u0027s condition, it is usually empty. Ryouga generally leads a nomadic lifestyle, and only occasionally manages to find it. His dog, however, has no such trouble finding her way and recognises him in both human and pig forms. It has been mentioned that Ranma helped to lead Ryouga home when they went to high school together.\",\"Description_6\":\"The combination of his poor sense of direction and his curse have regularly subjected Ryouga to imminent misery, constantly placing him lonely and lost in the wilderness, with tight food rations, or at the mercy of hungry predators. When first introduced, he is a very angry and seemingly unapproachable individual. Ryouga is emotional, more often than not following his heart rather than his head, though he has shown capability of using strategy when he is focused or lacking distractions. He is emotionally fragile, straightforward and naive. He regularly feels depressed, which thus far has served as the source for his chi projection. He is generally shy, humble and polite, especially around women. He is often easily tricked and used by some of the more manipulative characters and turns extremely grateful, loyal and self-sacrificing for any kindness offered to him.\",\"Description_7\":\"A running joke is that whenever female Ranma dons a disguise, no matter how transparent, Ryouga will nonetheless be fooled. Ranma has used this to his advantage to find out about any training Ryouga has been doing, to tease him, or to torment Ryouga during any dates with Akane to destroy the latter\\u0027s prospects.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Ryouga stands out in the crowd due to his regularly rough appearance. He spends much of his time wandering, often depressed over having to spend so much of his time alone in the wilderness, with the slightest rain turning him into a defenceless pig at the mercy of hungry humans or animals. His most notable characteristic is that, like his parents, and even his entire family, he has no sense of direction whatsoever. He is unable to go the right way, often sticking to the letter of any directions given to him, regardless of whether the path eventually turns. He has an inability to understand even the simplest of directions or draw any legible maps, once running the wrong way at the start of a three-legged race.\", \"Description_2\": \"This is not due to lack of motivation, however. For instance, on the way to a date, he was supposed to follow the edge of a lake, to reach a statue in plain sight directly in front of him. Instead, Ryouga follows a brook and gets lost again. In the anime, Maomolin the bakeneko possesses Ryouga and tries to lead him towards the girl he loves. However, Maomolin had as much trouble navigating as Ryouga himself even though the former was doing the thinking. In real world terms, he would be classified as suffering from autistic limitation or brain damage in this area. It is also possible that his lack of direction might be some form of family curse.\", \"Description_3\": \"In the anime this condition is worsened by Ryouga\'s ability to traverse obscene distances in surprisingly little time on foot, although how he does this is unknown. When the two problems are combined, it results in Ryouga having essentially no idea where he is at any given time, which allows him to miss his destinations by insane margins. In one case, he attempted to reach Hokkaido and instead ended up in Hong Kong. Luckily, he carries a backpack, which evidently contains essentials for survival in the wild.\", \"Description_4\": \"In the manga this is not as heavily implied to be a supernatural talent, at least not beyond his comical tendency to pop up at odd moments. He seems to need much longer travel times, and has not explicitly been seen to swiftly and randomly traverse continents under his own power. However, in his first appearance he quickly overshot Tokyo by 500 miles twice in a row, apparently within the span of one or two days, though no explicit reference was given. Through the aid of the Kinjakan, he also quickly made it all the way from Jusenkyo to Moscow and back while out to get some dumplings in Peking. His map was also once shown to contain a forest, a café, a road with a red car, the Tendo dojo, some African tribesmen, China, and France.\", \"Description_5\": \"Ryouga\'s family house is within sight of Mount Fuji, where his dog Shirokuro (Checkers in the English translation) and her puppies live. However, given the Hibiki family\'s condition, it is usually empty. Ryouga generally leads a nomadic lifestyle, and only occasionally manages to find it. His dog, however, has no such trouble finding her way and recognises him in both human and pig forms. It has been mentioned that Ranma helped to lead Ryouga home when they went to high school together.\", \"Description_6\": \"The combination of his poor sense of direction and his curse have regularly subjected Ryouga to imminent misery, constantly placing him lonely and lost in the wilderness, with tight food rations, or at the mercy of hungry predators. When first introduced, he is a very angry and seemingly unapproachable individual. Ryouga is emotional, more often than not following his heart rather than his head, though he has shown capability of using strategy when he is focused or lacking distractions. He is emotionally fragile, straightforward and naive. He regularly feels depressed, which thus far has served as the source for his chi projection. He is generally shy, humble and polite, especially around women. He is often easily tricked and used by some of the more manipulative characters and turns extremely grateful, loyal and self-sacrificing for any kindness offered to him.\", \"Description_7\": \"A running joke is that whenever female Ranma dons a disguise, no matter how transparent, Ryouga will nonetheless be fooled. Ranma has used this to his advantage to find out about any training Ryouga has been doing, to tease him, or to torment Ryouga during any dates with Akane to destroy the latter\'s prospects.\"}'),(1105,278901,'Hiroko','{}','{}'),(1106,256949,'Ichirou','{}','{}'),(1107,58321,'Jusenkyo Guide','{\"Description\":\"The Jusenkyo Guide is an unnamed man who works at Jusenkyo and usually warns anyone that comes there that they should not train there or they will fall under a grave curse. He knows the names of the hundreds of pools through the area, how long ago the spring became cursed, and the \\u0022tragic story\\u0022 behind each of them.\",\"(Source\":\"Ranma Wikia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Ranma Wikia)\", \"Description\": \"The Jusenkyo Guide is an unnamed man who works at Jusenkyo and usually warns anyone that comes there that they should not train there or they will fall under a grave curse. He knows the names of the hundreds of pools through the area, how long ago the spring became cursed, and the \\\"tragic story\\\" behind each of them.\"}'),(1108,258329,'Kichi','{}','{}'),(1109,10028,'Kunou, Kodachi','{\"Description\":\"Kodachi, known as \\u0022The Black Rose\\u0022 in the gymnastics community, is presented as Tatewaki Kuno\\u0027s sister and a student at St. Hebereke School for Girls (St. Bacchus School for Girls in the manga). This is in contrast to several members of the regular cast, who attend Furinkan\\u0027s mixed gender assemblage. As a master of \\u0022Martial Arts Rhythmic Gymnastics\\u0022 and captain of the school\\u0027s team, she often preemptively attacks her opponents with various weapons, including swords or a giant mallet to cripple them, thus winning by default. She calls it \\u0022fighting in all fairness before the match.\\u0022 Kodachi had seldom, if ever, lost a match before battling Ranma, a result of this practice. When these failed, she has also resorted to the use of more devious methods, once attempting to shake her foe\\u0027s hand with thumbtacks between her fingers. She is especially fond of using paralysis gas and sleeping powders on people, even when she has no apparent motivation to do so.\",\"Description_2\":\"Kodachi becomes enamoured with male Ranma after the latter acts as her \\u0027knight in shining armour\\u0027 by saving her from falling off the roof of the Tendo Dojo. Therefore, she is the only one of his suitors without some official or semi-official claim to him. Despite this, she considers him her lover and wants to make him her own through any means necessary. She and her brother have \\u0027opposite\\u0027 perspectives regarding this matter, since he despises Ranma\\u0027s male form due to the latter\\u0027s engagement to Akane and for \\u0027enslaving\\u0027 the mysterious \\u0027pigtailed girl.\\u0027 Correspondingly, Kodachi dislikes Ranma\\u0027s female form, whom she believes to be a romantic rival. Regardless of his dislike for Ranma, Tatewaki has enthusiastically given them his blessing to go steady since this would free Akane for himself. He secretly imagines that they would have a miserable life together.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Kodachi, known as \\\"The Black Rose\\\" in the gymnastics community, is presented as Tatewaki Kuno\'s sister and a student at St. Hebereke School for Girls (St. Bacchus School for Girls in the manga). This is in contrast to several members of the regular cast, who attend Furinkan\'s mixed gender assemblage. As a master of \\\"Martial Arts Rhythmic Gymnastics\\\" and captain of the school\'s team, she often preemptively attacks her opponents with various weapons, including swords or a giant mallet to cripple them, thus winning by default. She calls it \\\"fighting in all fairness before the match.\\\" Kodachi had seldom, if ever, lost a match before battling Ranma, a result of this practice. When these failed, she has also resorted to the use of more devious methods, once attempting to shake her foe\'s hand with thumbtacks between her fingers. She is especially fond of using paralysis gas and sleeping powders on people, even when she has no apparent motivation to do so.\", \"Description_2\": \"Kodachi becomes enamoured with male Ranma after the latter acts as her \'knight in shining armour\' by saving her from falling off the roof of the Tendo Dojo. Therefore, she is the only one of his suitors without some official or semi-official claim to him. Despite this, she considers him her lover and wants to make him her own through any means necessary. She and her brother have \'opposite\' perspectives regarding this matter, since he despises Ranma\'s male form due to the latter\'s engagement to Akane and for \'enslaving\' the mysterious \'pigtailed girl.\' Correspondingly, Kodachi dislikes Ranma\'s female form, whom she believes to be a romantic rival. Regardless of his dislike for Ranma, Tatewaki has enthusiastically given them his blessing to go steady since this would free Akane for himself. He secretly imagines that they would have a miserable life together.\"}'),(1110,7699,'Kunou, Tatewaki','{\"Description\":\"Tatewaki Kuno is an upperclassman at Furinkan High and was the big man on campus\\u2014at least until Ranma came along. Hailing from a very wealthy family, he is also captain of the kendo club and wields both his fortune and sword with equal ease. Given to spouting off Shakespearesque poetry (he quotes Confucius in the Japanese original), he is madly in love with Akane. He also falls for Ranma\\u0027s female half and never realizes that she is really his mortal enemy in girl form. He once overhears her called by name and attempts to write it down for future reference but never makes a connection and continues to refer to her as a \\u0022goddess in pig-tails\\u0022 for the entire series.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia, edited)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia, edited)\", \"Description\": \"Tatewaki Kuno is an upperclassman at Furinkan High and was the big man on campus—at least until Ranma came along. Hailing from a very wealthy family, he is also captain of the kendo club and wields both his fortune and sword with equal ease. Given to spouting off Shakespearesque poetry (he quotes Confucius in the Japanese original), he is madly in love with Akane. He also falls for Ranma\'s female half and never realizes that she is really his mortal enemy in girl form. He once overhears her called by name and attempts to write it down for future reference but never makes a connection and continues to refer to her as a \\\"goddess in pig-tails\\\" for the entire series.\"}'),(1111,2374,'Kuonji, Ukyo','{\"Description\":\"Ten years ago, on a training trip in the country, Genma stole Ukyo\\u0027s father\\u0027s okonomiyaki yatai (food cart), leaving her behind and breaking the arrangement he and her father made. However, before this Ranma and Ukyo were friends, though Ranma never knew she was a girl. Shamed and ridiculed by her peers, Ukyo decided she wouldn\\u0027t like boys, dressed and lived as one, and devoted herself to okonomiyaki-style martial arts. After a heated battle, Ranma discovers her true sex. Meanwhile, she discovers that he does not get along with his \\u0022uncute\\u0022 fianc\\u00E9e, Akane. They reconcile, and she falls in love with him again. Ranma still treats her as only an old friend, and her plots to win him over are usually less violent than those of his other suitors. Although she lives to cook okonomiyaki and runs a restaurant, \\u0022Ucchan\\u0027s,\\u0022 to that end, Ukyo would give it all up to marry Ranma.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Ten years ago, on a training trip in the country, Genma stole Ukyo\'s father\'s okonomiyaki yatai (food cart), leaving her behind and breaking the arrangement he and her father made. However, before this Ranma and Ukyo were friends, though Ranma never knew she was a girl. Shamed and ridiculed by her peers, Ukyo decided she wouldn\'t like boys, dressed and lived as one, and devoted herself to okonomiyaki-style martial arts. After a heated battle, Ranma discovers her true sex. Meanwhile, she discovers that he does not get along with his \\\"uncute\\\" fiancée, Akane. They reconcile, and she falls in love with him again. Ranma still treats her as only an old friend, and her plots to win him over are usually less violent than those of his other suitors. Although she lives to cook okonomiyaki and runs a restaurant, \\\"Ucchan\'s,\\\" to that end, Ukyo would give it all up to marry Ranma.\"}'),(1112,5210,'Mousse','{\"Description\":\"Mousse is a long-time friend of Shampoo, though she might not view it that way. He has been in love with her for most of his life, but she finds him annoying at best. He can\\u0027t see very well without his glasses, often mistaking someone for something else. He comes to Nerima in search of this \\u0022new fianc\\u00E9\\u0022 that Shampoo has, and he stays to attempt to woo his sweetheart. Shampoo rebuked his advances when they were children and this still holds true by Amazon law, even if he manages to defeat Ranma in combat, but he remains persistent. Now a waiter at the Cat Caf\\u00E9, he turns into a duck thanks to his own Jusenkyo curse. When in human form, his clothes contain weapons of drastic proportions, including needles, chains, swords, bombs, household appliances, and just about anything else imaginable. In duck form, Mousse can hide knives in his feathers.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Mousse is a long-time friend of Shampoo, though she might not view it that way. He has been in love with her for most of his life, but she finds him annoying at best. He can\'t see very well without his glasses, often mistaking someone for something else. He comes to Nerima in search of this \\\"new fiancé\\\" that Shampoo has, and he stays to attempt to woo his sweetheart. Shampoo rebuked his advances when they were children and this still holds true by Amazon law, even if he manages to defeat Ranma in combat, but he remains persistent. Now a waiter at the Cat Café, he turns into a duck thanks to his own Jusenkyo curse. When in human form, his clothes contain weapons of drastic proportions, including needles, chains, swords, bombs, household appliances, and just about anything else imaginable. In duck form, Mousse can hide knives in his feathers.\"}'),(1113,233165,'Narrator','{}','{}'),(1114,258331,'Noriko','{}','{}'),(1115,18771,'Ono, Toufuu','{\"Description\":\"Dr. Tofu Ono is the local chiropractor and often helps Akane and Ranma when they have bumps, bruises or dislocated joints from their many fights. He is very knowledgeable about martial arts techniques although he is never seen practicing. He helps Ranma discover a cure for Happosai\\u0027s \\u0022moxibustion,\\u0022 and Cologne\\u0027s \\u0022full body cat\\u0027s tongue\\u0022 techniques.\",\"Description_2\":\"Dr. Tofu is also deeply in love with Kasumi Tendo. In fact, whenever he is in her presence, his glasses fog over and he becomes nervous. He has injured quite a few of his patients when this happens.\",\"Description_3\":\"Dr. Tofu is well liked in the community and has many older clients. For a time he employed both Genma Saotome and Shampoo as assistants. He is often seen in the company of his skeleton, Betty, which he carries and moves as if it were a real person.\",\"Description_4\":\"At one time, Akane had a crush on Dr. Tofu, and he would often give her advice and support.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Dr. Tofu Ono is the local chiropractor and often helps Akane and Ranma when they have bumps, bruises or dislocated joints from their many fights. He is very knowledgeable about martial arts techniques although he is never seen practicing. He helps Ranma discover a cure for Happosai\'s \\\"moxibustion,\\\" and Cologne\'s \\\"full body cat\'s tongue\\\" techniques.\", \"Description_2\": \"Dr. Tofu is also deeply in love with Kasumi Tendo. In fact, whenever he is in her presence, his glasses fog over and he becomes nervous. He has injured quite a few of his patients when this happens.\", \"Description_3\": \"Dr. Tofu is well liked in the community and has many older clients. For a time he employed both Genma Saotome and Shampoo as assistants. He is often seen in the company of his skeleton, Betty, which he carries and moves as if it were a real person.\", \"Description_4\": \"At one time, Akane had a crush on Dr. Tofu, and he would often give her advice and support.\"}'),(1116,32560,'Sanzenin, Mikado','{\"Description\":\"Mikado Sanzenin is Shiratori Azusa\\u0027s skating partner.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Mikado Sanzenin is Shiratori Azusa\'s skating partner.\"}'),(1117,9913,'Saotome, Genma','{\"Description\":\"Genma Saotome is Ranma Saotome\\u0027s father and the sensei of the Saotome Dojo of Musabetsu Kakut\\u014D Ry\\u016B karate (\\u0022School of Indiscriminate Grappling,\\u0022 more commonly known in the West as \\u0022Anything Goes Martial Arts\\u0022). During the time when Genma took Ranma on a decade-long training voyage to improve their martial arts skills, he insisted on going to Jusenkyo in China - a place which he believed to be a training ground. However, because of Genma\\u0027s ignorance of the Chinese language, he did not realize that the ground was unfrequented because it was cursed. Genma realized all too late the mistake he made, after his son knocked him into a cursed spring during this fateful training session.\",\"Description_2\":\"Genma was knocked into Shonmaoniichuan (\\u718A\\u732B\\u6EBA\\u6CC9 Xi\\u00F3ngm\\u0101on\\u00EDqu\\u00E1n), the Spring of Drowned Panda. Due to the nature of the Jusenkyo curse, a victim who falls into the spring is cursed to turn into who or whatever drowned there when doused with cold water. Thus, whenever Genma is splashed with cold water, he becomes a giant panda. Hot water, as with the rest of the Jusenkyo-cursed characters, can change him back into human form.\",\"Despite the fact that he and his son were cursed, Genma still brought Ranma back to Japan to fulfill a marriage engagement with his longtime friend and fellow martial artist Soun Tendo, the terms of which were as follows\":\"Ranma would marry one of Soun\\u0027s daughters and carry on the Anything Goes School of Martial Arts.\",\"Description_3\":\"Genma and Soun decided that Soun\\u0027s youngest daughter Akane would one day marry Ranma after Akane\\u0027s sisters made the ruling on their own\\u2014against their will, at least at first. Genma currently resides in the Tendo Dojo along with Ranma, in the hopes that one day Ranma and Akane will get married and fulfill the agreement made by the two families. He spends most of his time playing Go or Shogi with Soun, although he briefly had a job at Dr. Tofu\\u0027s clinic.\",\"Description_4\":\"Unlike Ryoga, Mousse and Shampoo, Genma automatically regains his clothing when shifting back to normal, despite being too large to keep them in cursed form. The only other characters who shares a similar trait is Pantyhose Taro. Occasionally, primarily in the earliest stories, the top half of Genma\\u0027s gi and his glasses will also remain on him when he turns into a panda.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Genma Saotome is Ranma Saotome\'s father and the sensei of the Saotome Dojo of Musabetsu Kakutō Ryū karate (\\\"School of Indiscriminate Grappling,\\\" more commonly known in the West as \\\"Anything Goes Martial Arts\\\"). During the time when Genma took Ranma on a decade-long training voyage to improve their martial arts skills, he insisted on going to Jusenkyo in China - a place which he believed to be a training ground. However, because of Genma\'s ignorance of the Chinese language, he did not realize that the ground was unfrequented because it was cursed. Genma realized all too late the mistake he made, after his son knocked him into a cursed spring during this fateful training session.\", \"Description_2\": \"Genma was knocked into Shonmaoniichuan (熊猫溺泉 Xióngmāoníquán), the Spring of Drowned Panda. Due to the nature of the Jusenkyo curse, a victim who falls into the spring is cursed to turn into who or whatever drowned there when doused with cold water. Thus, whenever Genma is splashed with cold water, he becomes a giant panda. Hot water, as with the rest of the Jusenkyo-cursed characters, can change him back into human form.\", \"Description_3\": \"Genma and Soun decided that Soun\'s youngest daughter Akane would one day marry Ranma after Akane\'s sisters made the ruling on their own—against their will, at least at first. Genma currently resides in the Tendo Dojo along with Ranma, in the hopes that one day Ranma and Akane will get married and fulfill the agreement made by the two families. He spends most of his time playing Go or Shogi with Soun, although he briefly had a job at Dr. Tofu\'s clinic.\", \"Description_4\": \"Unlike Ryoga, Mousse and Shampoo, Genma automatically regains his clothing when shifting back to normal, despite being too large to keep them in cursed form. The only other characters who shares a similar trait is Pantyhose Taro. Occasionally, primarily in the earliest stories, the top half of Genma\'s gi and his glasses will also remain on him when he turns into a panda.\", \"Despite the fact that he and his son were cursed, Genma still brought Ranma back to Japan to fulfill a marriage engagement with his longtime friend and fellow martial artist Soun Tendo, the terms of which were as follows\": \"Ranma would marry one of Soun\'s daughters and carry on the Anything Goes School of Martial Arts.\"}'),(1118,2421,'Shampoo','{\"Description\":\"Shampoo met Ranma when Ranma (as a girl) and Genma (as a panda) drop into a contest in a village of the Joketsuzoku (\\u0022Chinese Amazons\\u0022) and the pair gorged themselves on the feast for the winner of the village\\u0027s martial arts contest. As village champion, Shampoo challenges them. Ranma defeats her, but according to Chinese Amazon tribal laws, if a female Amazon is defeated by a female outsider, she must give the outsider the \\u0022Kiss of Death,\\u0022 hunt her down to the ends of the Earth, and kill her. Ranma and Genma escape, and settle down in Nerima, Japan.\",\"Description_2\":\"Tracking Ranma to Japan, Shampoo encounters the male Ranma, who stops her from attacking Akane by knocking the ball off her bonbori and knocking her out. And if a female Amazon is defeated by a male outsider, she has to marry him. So she continues on the path of trying to marry male Ranma and kill female Ranma, until Ranma tricks her into thinking that the male side is a disguise for the female side.\",\"Description_3\":\"She returns to China to undergo specialized training from her great grandmother Cologne. It is at this time she falls into the Cursed Springs and receives her cat curse.\",\"Description_4\":\"Learning that Ranma is cursed as well, she goes back to Japan to marry him. She works with her great grandmother at the Neko Hanten as a waitress/cook/delivery girl.\",\"Description_5\":\"At first glance, Shampoo might seem like a bimbo, due to her simplified mode of speech, but she\\u0027s also had a limited amount of time to learn the Japanese language, after pursuing Ranma to his home country. This tendency may be exaggerated in western translations, although her grammar isn\\u0027t shown to improve after her second appearance, while she was presented as speaking fluent Chinese during a rooftop talk with Mousse. In the Memorial Book, Shampoo is described as \\u0027innocent and aggressive,\\u0027 which is an accurate summation of the dichotomy of her simultaneously cheerful, open, affectionate, hard-working, spiteful, sadistic, murderous and manipulative personality. Despite her frequently harsh treatment of other people and occasionally even towards Ranma himself, her love for him seems genuine.\",\"Description_6\":\"Having been trained in the martial art techniques of the Joketsuzoku since birth, with Cologne as her personal instructor and the young female village champion, Shampoo is highly skilled in unarmed combat, particularly involving speed and acrobatics, and is strong enough to casually walk through walls on a regular basis. Despite this, she uses a pair of bonbori as her primary weapons, but is also shown using sword, spear, bow, and a variety of polearms; however, she apparently doesn\\u0027t remotely compare to Ranma himself, and was completely outmatched and effortlessly overpowered the few times she\\u0027s seriously faced him in one-on-one combat.\",\"Description_7\":\"Beyond basic fighting ability, Shampoo has displayed knowledge of ventriloquism/voice imitation, shiatsu-induced unconsciousness, mind-control or memory loss, sleep-fighting, intuitive multi-step strategy, defense against enchanted herbs, Chinese cooking, and incredible tracking-skills enabling her to hunt Ranma from rural China to the east of Japan. She also has access to minor magic equipment, and is capable of using her bike to literally bounce across the city. Her true strength may lie in sheer versatility.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Shampoo met Ranma when Ranma (as a girl) and Genma (as a panda) drop into a contest in a village of the Joketsuzoku (\\\"Chinese Amazons\\\") and the pair gorged themselves on the feast for the winner of the village\'s martial arts contest. As village champion, Shampoo challenges them. Ranma defeats her, but according to Chinese Amazon tribal laws, if a female Amazon is defeated by a female outsider, she must give the outsider the \\\"Kiss of Death,\\\" hunt her down to the ends of the Earth, and kill her. Ranma and Genma escape, and settle down in Nerima, Japan.\", \"Description_2\": \"Tracking Ranma to Japan, Shampoo encounters the male Ranma, who stops her from attacking Akane by knocking the ball off her bonbori and knocking her out. And if a female Amazon is defeated by a male outsider, she has to marry him. So she continues on the path of trying to marry male Ranma and kill female Ranma, until Ranma tricks her into thinking that the male side is a disguise for the female side.\", \"Description_3\": \"She returns to China to undergo specialized training from her great grandmother Cologne. It is at this time she falls into the Cursed Springs and receives her cat curse.\", \"Description_4\": \"Learning that Ranma is cursed as well, she goes back to Japan to marry him. She works with her great grandmother at the Neko Hanten as a waitress/cook/delivery girl.\", \"Description_5\": \"At first glance, Shampoo might seem like a bimbo, due to her simplified mode of speech, but she\'s also had a limited amount of time to learn the Japanese language, after pursuing Ranma to his home country. This tendency may be exaggerated in western translations, although her grammar isn\'t shown to improve after her second appearance, while she was presented as speaking fluent Chinese during a rooftop talk with Mousse. In the Memorial Book, Shampoo is described as \'innocent and aggressive,\' which is an accurate summation of the dichotomy of her simultaneously cheerful, open, affectionate, hard-working, spiteful, sadistic, murderous and manipulative personality. Despite her frequently harsh treatment of other people and occasionally even towards Ranma himself, her love for him seems genuine.\", \"Description_6\": \"Having been trained in the martial art techniques of the Joketsuzoku since birth, with Cologne as her personal instructor and the young female village champion, Shampoo is highly skilled in unarmed combat, particularly involving speed and acrobatics, and is strong enough to casually walk through walls on a regular basis. Despite this, she uses a pair of bonbori as her primary weapons, but is also shown using sword, spear, bow, and a variety of polearms; however, she apparently doesn\'t remotely compare to Ranma himself, and was completely outmatched and effortlessly overpowered the few times she\'s seriously faced him in one-on-one combat.\", \"Description_7\": \"Beyond basic fighting ability, Shampoo has displayed knowledge of ventriloquism/voice imitation, shiatsu-induced unconsciousness, mind-control or memory loss, sleep-fighting, intuitive multi-step strategy, defense against enchanted herbs, Chinese cooking, and incredible tracking-skills enabling her to hunt Ranma from rural China to the east of Japan. She also has access to minor magic equipment, and is capable of using her bike to literally bounce across the city. Her true strength may lie in sheer versatility.\"}'),(1119,280814,'Shampoo\'s Father','{}','{}'),(1120,258330,'Shingo','{}','{}'),(1121,9259,'Shiratori, Azusa','{\"Description\":\"Azusa Shiratori is Sanzenin\\u0027s skating partner. A master of skating anything goes martial arts, she often likes cute things and gives them names.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Azusa Shiratori is Sanzenin\'s skating partner. A master of skating anything goes martial arts, she often likes cute things and gives them names.\"}'),(1122,9215,'Tendou, Souun','{\"Description\":\"Souun is the head of the Tendou household and one of the two families to practice Anything Goes Martial Arts. He\\u0027s a widower, left to single-handedly take care of his three daughters. He has a large house that is occasionally in need of repairs due to the fights that take place there. While he owns his own dojo, students have not been explicitly shown. Community representatives frequently approach him when they have problems with unusual phenomena, so this may provide some of it, and he has rented out the dojo for social meetings. However he is shown to be quite careful with the expenses and gets upset when Nabiki spends his savings on expensive gifts, or when Ranma throws the dinner on the floor. In the anime, he spends most of his time playing Shogi with his old training partner Genma. Souun is eager for his daughter to say she loves Ranma, or the other way around, to continue the legacy of his school. He\\u0027ll start announcing wedding plans if Ranma and Akane seem romantically involved. Souun is able to manifest himself as a ghostly, floating oni head, whenever he is upset, and often cries, \\u0022Oh, the humanity!\\u0022 in the anime. He generally assumes most incidents are Ranma\\u0027s fault. He\\u0027s shown as extremely protective of his children, and becomes sad if their affection is in doubt.\",\"Description_2\":\"Miss Hinako is attracted to him, but he is very loyal to his dead wife and visits her grave in memorial.\",\"(Source\":\"Wikipedia)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Wikipedia)\", \"Description\": \"Souun is the head of the Tendou household and one of the two families to practice Anything Goes Martial Arts. He\'s a widower, left to single-handedly take care of his three daughters. He has a large house that is occasionally in need of repairs due to the fights that take place there. While he owns his own dojo, students have not been explicitly shown. Community representatives frequently approach him when they have problems with unusual phenomena, so this may provide some of it, and he has rented out the dojo for social meetings. However he is shown to be quite careful with the expenses and gets upset when Nabiki spends his savings on expensive gifts, or when Ranma throws the dinner on the floor. In the anime, he spends most of his time playing Shogi with his old training partner Genma. Souun is eager for his daughter to say she loves Ranma, or the other way around, to continue the legacy of his school. He\'ll start announcing wedding plans if Ranma and Akane seem romantically involved. Souun is able to manifest himself as a ghostly, floating oni head, whenever he is upset, and often cries, \\\"Oh, the humanity!\\\" in the anime. He generally assumes most incidents are Ranma\'s fault. He\'s shown as extremely protective of his children, and becomes sad if their affection is in doubt.\", \"Description_2\": \"Miss Hinako is attracted to him, but he is very loyal to his dead wife and visits her grave in memorial.\"}'),(1123,3665,'Tendou, Kasumi','{\"Description\":\"Kasumi is the eldest of the Tendou girls and the most gentle of the lot. She graduated high school and spends most of her day looking after the Tendou household, acting as the family\\u0027s substitute \\u0022matriarch\\u0022 ever since her mother\\u0027s untimely death by cooking, cleaning, and helping her family.\",\"Description_2\":\"Kasumi is portrayed as the perfect lady, with a very sweet, caring, and self-sacrificing personality. Probably because of her extremely lovely nature, she is seldom affected by most of the crazy happenings around her and is wise in seeing through Nabiki\\u0027s schemes.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Kasumi is the eldest of the Tendou girls and the most gentle of the lot. She graduated high school and spends most of her day looking after the Tendou household, acting as the family\'s substitute \\\"matriarch\\\" ever since her mother\'s untimely death by cooking, cleaning, and helping her family.\", \"Description_2\": \"Kasumi is portrayed as the perfect lady, with a very sweet, caring, and self-sacrificing personality. Probably because of her extremely lovely nature, she is seldom affected by most of the crazy happenings around her and is wise in seeing through Nabiki\'s schemes.\"}'),(1124,3664,'Tendou, Nabiki','{\"Description\":\"Nabiki is the second daughter of Soun Tendou. The most important thing to her is money, and she would do anything to achieve it, including blackmailing her own family members. In some stories, she plays an important role in trying to extort money or placing bets just for her own amusement.\",\"Description_2\":\"She has a sarcastic, materialistic, egoistic, manipulative, sadistic, and completely amoral attitude that is a sharp contrast to her older sister.\",\"Description_3\":\"She can, in fact, be seen as the most intelligent character in both the manga and anime.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Nabiki is the second daughter of Soun Tendou. The most important thing to her is money, and she would do anything to achieve it, including blackmailing her own family members. In some stories, she plays an important role in trying to extort money or placing bets just for her own amusement.\", \"Description_2\": \"She has a sarcastic, materialistic, egoistic, manipulative, sadistic, and completely amoral attitude that is a sharp contrast to her older sister.\", \"Description_3\": \"She can, in fact, be seen as the most intelligent character in both the manga and anime.\"}'),(1125,258332,'Tomoyo','{}','{}'),(1126,57481,'Ono, Kin','{\"Description\":\"Dr. Tofu \\u0027s meddling mother decided it was time for him to settle down and get married. She pays a visit to his clinic and starts searching for bride with good, child-bearing hips.\",\"(Source\":\"Rumic World)\"}','{\"(Source\": \"Rumic World)\", \"Description\": \"Dr. Tofu \'s meddling mother decided it was time for him to settle down and get married. She pays a visit to his clinic and starts searching for bride with good, child-bearing hips.\"}'),(1127,222248,'Oumi, Shiori','{}','{}'),(1128,222247,'Yaotose, Hinako','{\"Description\":\"Hinako is a soft-spoken and shy high school girl who lives by herself after losing her family at a young age. Her blood has a unique scent that frequently attracts youkai to her. She has survivor\\u0027s guilt after the deaths of her family and wishes to die so she can reunite with them.\"}','{\"Description\": \"Hinako is a soft-spoken and shy high school girl who lives by herself after losing her family at a young age. Her blood has a unique scent that frequently attracts youkai to her. She has survivor\'s guilt after the deaths of her family and wishes to die so she can reunite with them.\"}'),(1129,229991,'Chiba, Ayame','{}','{}'),(1130,222249,'Yashiro, Miko','{}','{}'),(1131,267428,'Arel','{}','{}'),(1132,270334,'Lilia','{}','{}'),(1133,270333,'Raina','{}','{}'),(1134,275783,'Astaire','{}','{}'),(1135,282896,'Bacchus','{}','{}'),(1136,280948,'Barbarian','{}','{}'),(1137,280362,'Coachman','{}','{}'),(1138,282387,'Colette','{}','{}'),(1139,281521,'Deurgelda','{}','{}'),(1140,280951,'Diehl','{}','{}'),(1141,283300,'Dione','{}','{}'),(1142,280947,'Dual Swordswoman','{}','{}'),(1143,283302,'Dumble','{}','{}'),(1144,280361,'Evans','{}','{}'),(1145,282640,'Examiner','{}','{}'),(1146,275781,'Fara','{}','{}'),(1147,280535,'Georg','{}','{}'),(1148,280536,'Gio','{}','{}'),(1149,283304,'Green Academy\'s Headmaster','{}','{}'),(1150,283301,'Grid','{}','{}'),(1151,282390,'Hengel','{}','{}'),(1152,282386,'Kaito','{}','{}'),(1153,275151,'Kuufa','{}','{}'),(1154,282389,'Latalia','{}','{}'),(1155,275782,'Leon','{}','{}'),(1156,281657,'Magic Swordswoman','{}','{}'),(1157,280537,'Masamune','{}','{}'),(1158,275784,'Mira','{}','{}'),(1159,280949,'Moderator','{}','{}'),(1160,280259,'Rod','{}','{}'),(1161,282639,'Royce','{}','{}'),(1162,280950,'Shield Swordsman','{}','{}'),(1163,283299,'Skike','{}','{}'),(1164,282641,'Teacher of the Green Academy','{}','{}'),(1165,243453,'Andrey, Krai','{}','{}'),(1166,280416,'Alekko','{}','{}'),(1167,257644,'Anger, Sven','{}','{}'),(1168,283007,'Apoclys, Telm','{}','{}'),(1169,260216,'Argent, Kris','{}','{}'),(1170,283004,'Argman, Franz','{}','{}'),(1171,283003,'Atolm Zebrudia, Murina','{}','{}'),(1172,283001,'Atolm Zebrudia, Rodrick','{}','{}'),(1173,280649,'Auden, Mary','{}','{}'),(1174,282151,'Barrel, Geffroy','{}','{}'),(1175,282152,'Barrel, Carton','{}','{}'),(1176,257642,'Black, Sophia','{}','{}'),(1177,254352,'Bush, Gilbert','{}','{}'),(1178,257643,'Cochlear, Noctus','{}','{}'),(1179,260215,'Fulgor, Lapis','{}','{}'),(1180,260218,'Gladis, Éclair','{}','{}'),(1181,259441,'Hail, Arnold','{}','{}'),(1182,281201,'Hailo','{}','{}'),(1183,280650,'Henning, Artbaran','{}','{}'),(1184,260221,'Jaster','{}','{}'),(1185,259442,'Killiam','{}','{}'),(1186,281199,'Kuro','{}','{}'),(1187,260220,'Laria, Eigh','{}','{}'),(1188,260936,'Matthis','{}','{}'),(1189,256525,'Melnes, Isabella','{}','{}'),(1190,283364,'Munk, Kechachakka','{}','{}'),(1191,251337,'Narrator','{}','{}'),(1192,258209,'Nori, Marrietta','{}','{}'),(1193,256055,'Noss, Kaina','{}','{}'),(1194,281202,'Orc','{}','{}'),(1195,283005,'Purapos, Rosemary','{}','{}'),(1196,254349,'Renfied, Eva','{}','{}'),(1197,256056,'Rodin, Ark','{}','{}'),(1198,251335,'Rogier, Lucia','{}','{}'),(1199,254350,'Runebeck, Rhuda','{}','{}'),(1200,282150,'Ryuul